{"TopicId":129646,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"I thought this was a cool blender animation.","CreatedByName":"GDJ","CreatedById":58462,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-10T17:04:43Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"GDJ","CreatedById":58462,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-10T17:04:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=At0w3pnIVgc\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=At0w3pnIVgc\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt\u0027s all the major moons and planets of our Solar System in scale to one another.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nFor KSP reference, Kerbin is about the size of Eris (give or take a itty bitty bit).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-10T17:10:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNIce... Would be kewl if someone replicated that for KSP\u0027s Kerbol system...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GDJ","CreatedById":58462,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-10T18:36:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s another one, comparing our planets, then stars.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HEheh1BH34Q\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HEheh1BH34Q\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nOur sun is literally a dwarf in the grand scheme of things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SuperFastJellyfish","CreatedById":57985,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-10T22:35:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s a flash thingy in the same vein:\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022http://htwins.net/scale2/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://htwins.net/scale2/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-11T10:47:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw an error. Phobos and Deimos sizes are all wrong. They\u0027re tiny asteroids, not huge lumps as shown in the video.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Findthepin1","CreatedById":139989,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-11T21:53:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd they show Earth as being tiny compared to Uranus or Neptune. It\u0027s actually similar to the comparison between Earth and Moon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GDJ","CreatedById":58462,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-11T22:04:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222356956\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022129646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452509242\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002279159\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, lajoswinkler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw an error. Phobos and Deimos sizes are all wrong. They\u0027re tiny asteroids, not huge lumps as shown in the video.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, you wouldn\u0027t be able to see them if they were scale, eh? The video producers probably wanted to show what they looked like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222357654\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022129646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452549182\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139989\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Findthepin1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Findthepin1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd they show Earth as being tiny compared to Uranus or Neptune. It\u0027s actually similar to the comparison between Earth and Moon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, they showed that. Uranus and Neptune are about 4X the size of Earth, and the Earth is about 4X the size of the moon. It may not be spot-on, but close enough.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n-EDIT- I double checked it, yeah the animation is out a bit. Oh well. It\u0027s just a video.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-11T22:15:43Z\u0022 title=\u002201/11/2016 10:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 11, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by GDJ\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-12T09:17:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222357676\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022129646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452549848\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258462\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GDJ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, GDJ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, you wouldn\u0027t be able to see them if they were scale, eh? The video producers probably wanted to show what they looked like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the point is to show stuff to scale, then it\u0027s wrong. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut yeah, they wouldn\u0027t be visible at such poor resolution. \u003Ca href=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/7/79/Mars_Moons_Orbit_distance.jpeg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EThis is to scale.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}